OL,7,FAid is classified largely as day-to-
OL,8,Fday operational expenditure whereas
OL,9,Fmuch of defence is capital. And since
OL,10,Fthe primary binding fiscal rule is to
OL,11,Fbalance day-to-day spending with tax
OL,12,Frevenues, cutting development spending
OL,13,Fby #6 billion generates #6 billion of
OL,14,Fheadroom, even when that #6 billion
OL,15,Fgoes to the Ministry of Defence to
OL,16,Fspend on planes and ships.
